					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm working on a little test demo to gain some understanding into the NES hardware (having learned to program in assembly on the C-64). I'd like to program a full-blown demoscenish demo with some simple effects I've done on different platforms.
<br />
<br />What I'd like to know is what is the best/easiest/fastest/whatever way to wait for a scanline? What I mean is, that I'd like, for example, to show on the top half a scrolling picture (one 4k of CHR-ROM) and on the bottom half some text (the other half).
<br />
<br />Now, I know that I can change the "graphics page" by using $2000. But how can I change it in midscreen? Also, should this also enable me to use different values for scrolling ($2005) on the different halves of the screen?
<br />
<br />EDIT: I'm talking about raster splits, of course.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=865">visy</a> on Sat Aug 12, 2006 5:58 am, edited 1 time in total.</span>
