				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know where the gray-color parts could be coming from, unless you're accidentally (or purposely) enabling the grayscale mode.  Otherwise there is gray in your palette.  If you shut the screen off manually (I think you won't need to, but I suppose you could do the whole thing with the screen off), whatever palette byte the VRAM pointer is set to will be used as the background color.  I'd recommend using Nintendulator's debugger to step through the code, it has the very handy feature of telling you when it's in hblank.</div>

